The existence of shells is inherently linked to that of computing.
Back in the day, developers all agreed that communicating with a computer using 1/0 switches was highly irritating.
The logical next step was to invent a way to communicate through interactive command lines in a language that was somewhat close to human language.
With Minishell, we will travel to the past and face the problems that we could have had at a time when Windows did not yet exist.
